dent. F-TYPE-004 is a subset (NaN-specific unwraps). FILES: All .rs files in crates/. SEVERITY: Medium. WAVE: 1. EFFORT: 4h.; ASSESSMENT FINDING: F(S) Harvest Quality Component (H) Cold Start Problem — bilateral.rs lines 870-887. The H component (weight 0.13) defaults to 0.0 (unmeasured) when no session telemetry exists. This artificially suppresses F(S) by up to 13% on cold starts and at the beginning of every session until the first observation is recorded. H computes methodology score M(t) from session activity (task creation, observations, spec-language usage). Before any activity, H=0.0 rather than a neutral baseline (e.g., 0.5). This means early-stage projects or fresh sessions show F(S) approximately 0.6 even with perfect validation/coverage. The distinction between 'not yet measured' and 'measured as 0.0' is lost. FIX: Two options: (1) Default H to 0.5 (neutral prior) when no session telemetry exists. (2) Track 'not yet measured' separately from 'measured as 0.0' and exclude unmeasured components from weighted sum (renormalize remaining weights). Option 2 is cleaner but requires changes to the F(S) display logic. VERIFICATION: (1) Initialize empty store. (2) Compute F(S) before any observations. (3) Before fix: H=0.0 suppresses score. After fix: H excluded or defaulted. INTERACTS WITH: F(S) stagnation (H=0.0 contributes to depression), DOGFOOD-2 (external project cold start hits this immediately). TRACES TO: INV-BILATERAL-003 (F(S) component semantics).; AUDIT F-SPEC-004: Specification namespaces vs implementation module mapping is undocumented. PROBLEM: The spec defines 23 namespaces. The implementation has ~47 source files. The mapping is partially documented in doc comments but not maintained as a formal cross-reference. Notable many-to-many cases: GUIDANCE -> guidance.rs + methodology.rs + routing.rs + context.rs (split across 4 files), COHERENCE -> bilateral.rs + coherence.rs (overlapping names confuse). JUSTIFICATION: C5 (Traceability) requires explici