esting without object construction. Consistent with ADR-STORE-015. These strengths are load-bearing — they enable the formal guarantees the project's vision requires. Do not regress on any of these. TRACES TO: C1 (append-only enforcement via typestate), C4 (CRDT proofs), C7 (self-bootstrap via genesis determinism proof).; ASSESSMENT FINDING: Drift Component Φ Linear Scaling Problem — bilateral.rs line 1144-1145, trilateral.rs lines 192-220. Divergence Φ counts total boundary gaps but does not weight by severity or coverage quality. A spec with falsification but no impl counts the same as a spec with neither. D = 1 - Φ/Φ_max is linear, where Φ_max = entity_count. As the project grows (more entities → larger Φ_max), marginal improvements from closing individual gaps have diminishing returns on D. Closing 10 gaps when Φ_max=100 gives ΔD=+0.10. Closing 10 gaps when Φ_max=1000 gives ΔD=+0.01. This creates a structural bias against convergence in large stores — the larger the store grows, the harder it is for gap closure to move F(S). FIX options: (1) Weight gaps by formality level (unfalsifiable spec gap counts less than well-specified gap). (2) Use log-scale for Φ: D = 1 - log(Φ+1)/log(Φ_max+1). (3) Normalize by current-stage entities only (exclude Phase E specs from Phase B denominator). Option 3 is most principled — only measure convergence against what should be converged at the current phase. VERIFICATION: Compare D component across sessions with linear vs log vs phase-scoped formulas. Phase-scoped should show movement where linear shows stagnation. INTERACTS WITH: F(S) stagnation (D is 0.18 weight), structural ceiling risk (D's linear scaling may be a contributor), verification sprint (gap closure impact depends on Φ_max). TRACES TO: INV-BILATERAL-003 (F(S) component semantics), ADR-FOUNDATION-014.; ASSESSMENT FINDING: Concept Collapse Root Cause — Emergent concepts collapsing to single cluster. Root cause: JOIN_THRESHOLD = 0.20 with HashEmbedder. The HashEmbedder produces embeddings via BLAKE3 word hashing — deterministic but purely word-overlap based. In a project where most observations share vocabulary (store, entity, spec, implementation, convergence), all observations exceed 0.20 cosine similarity. The agglomerative clustering merges all high-similarity pairs, eventually collapsing to 1 mega-cluster. Evidence: no test prevents single-concept collapse; test crystallize_three_similar_observations only checks at least 1 concept formed. This is a measurement problem, not a conceptual one — observations genuinely contain distinct concepts but the embedding cannot distinguish semantic domains sharing vocabulary. Solution: replace HashEmbedder with TF-IDF weighted embeddings using store vocabulary statistics. IDF computed from the store's own attribute/value corpus downweights common terms (store, entity) and surfaces distinguishing terms. No external ML dependency needed. Alternative: raise JOIN_THRESHOLD to 0.35-0.45 (quick fix but breaks detection of genuinely similar observations). Better: TF-IDF + entropy regularization in crystallization + maximum cluster size cap. VERIFICATION: After TF-IDF implementation, run concept clustering on current 130+ observations. Should produce 5-15 distinct concepts instead of 1-3. DOGFOOD-2 concept quality should improve from baseline. INTERACTS WITH: OBSERVER-6 (ontology discovery blocked by collapse), DOGFOOD-2 score (hash embedder identified as bottleneck), seed assembly (concept-aware seeding depends on meaningful concepts). TRACES TO: OBSERVER-6 (ontology discovery loop), INV-CONCEPT-001.; AUDIT CROSS-CUTTING-SYNTHESIS: The central diagnosis — C8 is both the deepest problem and has the clearest solution path. OBSERVATION: Across all 10 audit dimensions, C8 (Substrate Independence) is the unifying thread. The LIVE index bug (F-INV-001) is a correctness defect; the verification gaps (F-SPEC-001) are coverage deficits. But C8 violations are architectural — they determine whether braid ac