to the merged pass or read from telemetry.; Session entity: :task/t-588ed0fa; ASSESSMENT FINDING: DOGFOOD-2 Score 3.48/10 — External Validation Signal. DOGFOOD-2 tested braid on an external Go CLI project and scored 3.48/10. This is the most important empirical data point in the project because it tests the core hypothesis on non-self data. Key bottleneck identified: hash embedder. The score tells us: (1) harvest/seed lifecycle is not yet production-ready for external projects. (2) The hash embedder's word-overlap semantics fail on diverse vocabulary (Go CLI has different terms than Rust epistemology runtime). (3) Concept clustering produces meaningless results on external data (concept collapse confirmed). (4) Seed assembly may over-weight DDIS-specific relevance signals. The 3.48/10 score is not a failure of the architecture — it's a measurement of the gap between internal self-use (where 46 sessions of tuning have created implicit optimization) and general use. The fix path: (1) Replace hash embedder (Priority 6), (2) S0-CLOSE external validation (Priority 4) with rubric-based scoring, (3) Compare before/after TF-IDF on same external project. VERIFICATION: Re-run DOGFOOD-2 after TF-IDF embedder replacement. Target: score ≥ 6/10. If still < 5/10 after embedder fix, the bottleneck is elsewhere (seed assembly, harvest extraction, or fundamental approach). INTERACTS WITH: S0-CLOSE proposal, single-customer overfitting risk, concept collapse, hash embedder replacement. TRACES TO: SEED.md Stage 0 success criterion, C8 (substrate independence in practice).; ASSESSMENT FINDING: Hypothesis Ledger Degradation — Open Calibration Loop. Mean error degraded from 0.254 (Session 036, 24 manually completed hypotheses) to 0.521 (current, 145/273 completed). Root cause: the ledger records predictions via record_hypotheses_with_type() at harvest time, but outcome matching requires explicit :action/outcome datoms that are almost never generated. The CLI braid close command does not w