ap. PROBLEM: braid status reports '265 current-stage INVs untested -> add L2+ witness.' The specification defines 201 invariants across 23 namespaces. Estimated per-namespace test coverage: STORE ~60%, QUERY ~70%, SCHEMA ~50%, RESOLUTION ~40%, HARVEST/SEED ~30%, TRILATERAL/BILATERAL ~20%, TOPOLOGY ~60%, GUIDANCE/BUDGET ~15%. 2,043 tests exist but many test implementation behavior ('does transact add a datom?') rather than specification invariants ('is INV-STORE-001 satisfied for all reachable states?'). No formal mapping from tests to INVs exists. JUSTIFICATION: INV-WITNESS-011 (Verification Completeness Guard) requires every invariant to have a witness. The gap between 'test exists' and 'invariant is witnessed' is the difference between accidental coverage and deliberate verification. A test that exercises INV-STORE-001 incidentally (because transact happens to be append-only) provides less confidence than a test explicitly constructed to falsify INV-STORE-001 (by attempting deletion and verifying it fails). SOLUTION: (1) Create coverage matrix: INV-ID -> test name -> witness level (L0/L1/L2/L3). (2) Prioritize Stage 0 INVs (STORE, SCHEMA, QUERY, LAYOUT) for L2+ witnesses. (3) Add #[doc = \"Witnesses: INV-STORE-001\"] to tests. VERIFICATION: Coverage matrix shows 100% L2+ for Stage 0 INVs. DEPENDENCIES: Complements F-TEST-001 (coverage matrix gap). Interacts with F-FORMAL-001 (Kani coverage). FILES: spec/ (all), tests/ (all). SEVERITY: High. WAVE: 3. EFFORT: 40h.; AUDIT F-FORMAL-002: Stateright model has 1 ignored test — coverage gap. PROBLEM: The Stateright model checker (tests/stateright_model.rs) has 10 passing tests and 1 ignored: transact_coherence_no_undetected_contradictions. The reason for ignoring is not documented. The test references INV-COHERENCE-002 (no undetected contradictions). JUSTIFICATION: An ignored test is a coverage gap. It may cover an unimplemented invariant, may be intermittently failing, or may have been disabled during a refactor and neve