verage inflated. After fix: coverage accurate. Measure F(S) before and after — C component should drop slightly, giving a more honest baseline. INTERACTS WITH: F(S) stagnation (inflated C masks true gap), saw-tooth validation (can't validate model if measurement is wrong), verification sprint (need accurate baseline before sprint). TRACES TO: C6 (falsifiability — the measurement itself must be falsifiable), INV-BILATERAL-002 (coverage accuracy).; PERF AUDIT FINDING P2-TASKS: all_tasks(store) is called 4 separate times during a single braid status invocation — from task_counts(), compute_ready_set(), methodology_gaps(), and compute_routing_with_calibration(). Each call does a full O(N) datom scan filtering for :task/id, then for each task entity calls task_summary() which iterates entity datoms. At 105K datoms with ~1400 tasks, this is 4 × (105K + 1400 × avg_datoms_per_task) ≈ 500K iterations. FIX: Compute all_tasks once in StatusSnapshot, pass the result to all 4 consumers. This is the same compute-once pattern that StatusSnapshot already uses for fitness and coherence. The Vec<TaskSummary> is ~50KB — trivial to pass by reference. DEEPER FIX: Materialize task counts incrementally in MaterializedViews. The current views.task_open/in_progress/closed counters are APPROXIMATE — they count all historical :task/status Assert datoms rather than live (current) status. Fix: track live status via the LIVE view (latest-wins per entity), maintain accurate counters. Verification: (A) all_tasks called exactly once per status (grep for call sites, or add debug counter). (B) Materialized task counts match all_tasks().len() grouped by status. Traces to INV-STORE-012, ADR-STORE-006. Depends on nothing.; AUDIT F-C8-004: Guidance system hardcodes Basin Competition model — 14,137 LOC of DDIS methodology in kernel. PROBLEM: The guidance system spans guidance.rs (7,119 LOC) + methodology.rs (1,715 LOC) + routing.rs (2,879 LOC) + context.rs (2,424 LOC) = 14,137 LOC combined, 17% of the 83,